sflock - simple finger screen locker
============================
simple screen locker utility for X, unlock by fprintd-verify


Requirements
------------
In order to build sflock you need the Xlib header files.
And you MUST have fprintd installed on your system, otherwise
you CANNOT unlock your screen.
if you have problem in unlocking, press CTRL+ALT+F1 and log 
into the console, then killall sflock. 

Installation
------------
Edit config.mk to match your local setup (sflock is installed into
the /usr/local namespace by default).

Afterwards enter the following command to build and install sflock
(if necessary as root):

    make clean install


Running sflock
-------------
Simply invoke the 'sflock' command. To get out of it, simply swipe 
your right-index finger(the default value of fprintd-verify command).
